        <div style="width:60%;display:inline-block;vertical-align:text-top;padding:1.2%">
        <p>INSTRUCTIONS</p>
        <p>all measurements can be entered as whole numbers or as decimals (fractions will not work). do not round your measurements; be as precise as you can!</p>
        <p>it does not matter whether you use inches or centimeters - just use the same one for all four measurements.</p>
        <p>for sweater measurements, it is recommended that you measure a sweater that fits well, rather than entering body measurements.</p>
        <p><ol>
                <li>using whatever needles and yarn you want to use for your sweater, knit a 20-stitch x 20-row swatch</li>
                <li>measure a 10-stitch span of the swatch (laid flat) and enter its width into the appropriate box</li>
                <li>measure a 10-row span of the swatch (laid flat) and enter its length into the appropriate box</li>
                <li>measure the width (not circumference) of the sweater body and enter that into the appropriate box</li>
                <li>measure the length of the sweater body from collar to waistband (inclusive) and enter that into the appropriate box</li>
                <li>measure the width (not circumference) of one sleeve near the armpit and enter that into the appropriate box</li>
                <li>measure the length of the sleeve from armpit to cuff (including the cuff) and enter that into the appropriate box<li>
                <li>measure the circumference of your head at the widest part and enter that into the appropriate box<li>
                <li>hit "calculate"</li>
                <li>mark down the output on your copy of the <a href="http://www.ravelry.com/designers/becky-lee" target="_blank">entwining pattern</a> and get knitting!</li>
            </ol>
        </p>

        </div>


        <div style="width:15%;display:inline-block;vertical-align:text-top;padding:1.2%">
        <p>INPUT</p>
        <form id="inputForm" action="form_action.asp">
            <p>width of ten stitches: <input type="number" name="inputGW"></p>
            <p>length of ten rows: <input type="number" name="inputGL"></p>
            <p>width of body: <input type="number" name="inputBW"></p>
            <p>length of body: <input type="number" name="inputBL"></p>
            <p>width of sleeve: <input type="number" name="inputSW"></p>
            <p>length of sleeve: <input type="number" name="inputSL"></p>
            <p>circumference of head: <input type="number" name="inputHead"></p>
        </form>
        
        <button onclick="myFunction()">calculate</button>

        <script>
        
        input = document.getElementById("inputForm");
        input.addEventListener("mousewheel", function(evt){ evt.preventDefault(); });

        function myFunction() {
            var x = document.getElementById("inputForm");
            var inputGW = x.elements[0].value;
            var inputGL = x.elements[1].value;
            var inputBW = x.elements[2].value;
            var inputBL = x.elements[3].value;
            var inputSW = x.elements[4].value;
            var inputSL = x.elements[5].value;
            var bodyWidth = Math.round(inputBW / inputGW * 10);
            var bodyLength = Math.round(inputBL / inputGL * 10);
            var sleeveCirc = Math.round(inputSW / inputGW * 20); //times 20 to turn width into circumference
            var sleeveLength = Math.round(inputSL / inputGL * 10);
            var collarCirc = inputHead / inputGW * 10;
            collarCirc += (4 - (collarCirc % 4)); //this and...
            var raglanEnd = bodyWidth*2 + sleeveCirc*2; //this will always be even, so...
            bodyWidth += ((raglanEnd - collarCirc) % 8)/2; //first part of this is too, and stitches can always be divided evenly betwen front & back of body
            raglanEnd = bodyWidth*2 + sleeveCirc*2; //recalculate after adjusting bodyWidth
            var raglanIncreases = raglanEnd - collarCirc;
            
            var sleeveStart = ;
            var bodyStart = ;
            
            
            
            var ribbingStart = "KKPP";
            
            
            
            
            
            var outputB = Math.round(footW / gaugeW * 10);
            outputB += (outputB % 2);
            var outputA = Math.round(outputB / 4);
            outputA += ((outputB - outputA) % 4);
            var outputD = (outputB / 2) + outputA + 2; //added two. diff between D and 1/2B will always be even.
            var DPrime = (outputA / 2) + 1; // each side!!
            var outputE = DPrime + 1;
            var outputG = outputA / 2;
            var outputF = (outputD - outputG - (DPrime * 2)) / 2; //(outputD - (1.5 * outputA)) / 2
            var outputC = Math.round((footL / gaugeL * 10) - ((outputB - outputA) / 2) - (outputD - (outputB / 2)) - (outputF * 2)); //didn't subtract length from cast-on + first knitting row - leaving those in to account for three-dimensionality of toe!
            var outputH = outputB / 2 + 1;
            
            
            document.getElementById("outputA").innerHTML = collarCirc;
            document.getElementById("outputB").innerHTML = ribbingStart;
            document.getElementById("outputC").innerHTML = sleeveStart;
            document.getElementById("outputD").innerHTML = bodyStart;
            document.getElementById("outputE").innerHTML = sleeveStart;
            document.getElementById("outputF").innerHTML = outputF;
            document.getElementById("outputG").innerHTML = outputG;
            document.getElementById("outputH").innerHTML = outputH;
        }
